    "The data processing corresponds to the standard procedure for any conventional analyses, hence for further details we refer the reader to Sagehorn et al. (2023).",
    "For further processing with SHERPA the data was reduced to 0 ms to 1500 ms.",
    "A CNN classifier with four convolutional layers alternating with Max Pooling layers, and Batch Normalization in the beginning and end was used for training.",
    "Furthermore, after flattening, four dense layers were added.",
    "The convolutional layers have ascending filter sizes between 16 and 128 filters, a kernel size of 50, Gaussian error linear unit (GELU) activation, and L2 regularization."
